<%== content_tag(:h2, '15. Cookie Policy', id: :cookie_policy) %>
<p>Tourney Opportunities uses cookies and/or similar technologies on Tourney Opportunities. A cookie is a small file which is being installed on a web page or application to collect information. The cookie collects all kinds of information, for example on the use of Tourney Opportunities. With this information, Tourney Opportunities can provide you with the best Tourney Opportunities experience.</p>
<p>In this cookie policy, we will explain what cookies we use and for what purpose we use cookies.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Session Cookie. We use a cookie to check if you are logged in or not. Without accepting cookies, you will not be able to access the restricted pages of the site.</li>
  <li>Locale Cookie. If you choose a locale, we store this choice in a cookie to ensure your preference is preserved across pages. Without accepting cookies, you will not be able to change your locale.</li>
  <li>Cookie acceptance cookie. We use a cookie to mark your acceptance of cookies. Without accepting cookies, you will be asked to accept cookies each time you access Tourney Opportunities.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Managing cookies</h3>
<p>You can always change your cookie preferences by:</p>
<ul>
<li>opening the "Help" menu on the browser menu bar. Most browsers will tell you how you can disable or delete cookies or set your browser to alert you when cookies are being sent to your computer;</li>
<li>visiting your mobile device developer's website or reviewing your device manual. Most mobile device developers will tell you how you can manage the settings on your mobile device to opt out of and/or delete cookies from your mobile device, or to limit the use of and/or opt out of targeted advertising; or</li>
<li>visiting <%= link_to 'NAI Consumer Opt Out', 'http://optout.networkadvertising.org/' %> and/or <%= link_to 'WebChoices Tool', 'http://optout.aboutads.info/' %>, or, if you are in the EU, <%= link_to 'Your Online Choices', 'http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/' %>, for choices to opt out of advertising.</li>
</ul>
